Executive Profile
Peter   Harf  Chairman and Chief Executive Officer, Joh. A. Benckiser GmbHAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 10 different industries.See Board Relationships71--
Background

		Mr. Peter Harf has been the Chief Executive Officer and Senior Partner at JAB Holdings B.V. since January 1988 and a Managing Director of the Selling Shareholder since August 1997. Mr. Harf has been the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer at Joh. A. Benckiser GmbH since 1996. He serves as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer at Calvin Klein Cosmetics Corporation. He is a co-founder of Delete Blood Cancer DKMS and serves as its Executive Chairman. He served as the ... Chief Executive Officer at Coty Inc. from 1993 to 2001. He joined JAB in 1981 as Senior Vice President of International Operations. He served as a Senior Vice President of International Operations from January 1981 to May 1982 and then served as an Executive Vice President of Consumer Products Division from May 1982 to January 1987. He served as the Chairman and a Member of the Management Board of Benckiser N.V. since August 1997. He served as Senior Vice President of Corporate Planning at Application Engineering Group (AEG), Telefunken, Frankfurt, Germany. He began his career at the Boston Consulting Group (BCG), based in both San Francisco, California and Munich, Germany. He served as Vice Chairman of the Management Board of JAB GmbH from January 1987 to January 1988. He serves as the Chairman of Lancaster Group US LLC and JAB Luxury. He has been the Non-Executive Chairman at Jimmy Choo PLC since September 2014. He served as the Chairman of Anheuser-Busch InBev SA/NV from 2002 to April 25, 2012. Mr. Harf served as the Chairman of Coty Inc., since 2001. He served as the Chairman of Reckitt Benckiser Pakistan Limited. He served as the Chairman of the Supervisory Board at Benckiser N.V. since August 1997. He served as Deputy Chairman of Reckitt Benckiser Group PLC from 1999 to December 21, 2015. He serves as Vice Chairman of the Supervisory Board of the non-profit DKMS German Bone Marrow Donor Database. He serves as a Director of Joh. A. Benckiser GmbH. He serves as Director of Reckitt Benckiser Pakistan Limited and Peet's Coffee & Tea, Inc. He serves as a Non-Executive Director of D.E Master Blenders 1753 N.V. He has been a Director of Interbrew S.A. since 2002 and Coty Inc. since 1996. He served as a Director of Kimberly-Clark Tissue Company (Scott Paper Co) since 1990. He served as a Director of Brunswick Corporation from 1996 to March 13, 2007 and Anheuser-Busch InBev SA/NV from 2002 to April 25, 2012. He served as a Director at Burger King Worldwide, Inc., until November 15, 2011 and Burger King Holdings, Inc, from 2010 to 2011. He served as a Member of the Supervisory Board at Benckiser N.V. since May 13, 1999. Mr. Harf received his MBA degree in 1974 from the Harvard Business School. Mr. Harf  holds both a Diploma and a Doctorate in Economics from the University of Cologne, where he taught as an Assistant Professor.Read Full Background




