Insider Activity


Individual




Peter Harf



Dr. Peter Harf is Non-Executive Chairman at Jimmy Choo Plc, Chairman at JAB Luxury GmbH, Chairman at Deutsche Stiftung Leben Spenden, Chairman & Chief Executive Officer at Joh. A Benckiser SE, Chairman at Coty Italia SpA, Chief Executive Officer at Donata Holding SE, Chief Executive Officer at Parentes SE, Chief Executive Officer at JAB Holdings II BV, Executive Chairman at DKMS Deutsche Knochenmarkspenderdatei, Co-Chairman at JAB Holding Co. SARL, Chief Executive Officer at Lucresca SE, Chief Executive Officer at Agnaten SE, Chairman at Belstaff Group SA, Chairman at Bally International AG, and Chairman at Delete Blood Cancer. He is on the Board of Directors at D.E. Master Blenders 1753 BV, Coty, Inc., and Koninklijke Douwe Egberts BV.
Dr. Harf was previously employed as Chairman by Anheuser-Busch InBev SA, Deputy Chairman by Reckitt Benckiser Group Plc, a Principal by The Boston Consulting Group, Inc., and Senior Vice President-Corporate Planning by AEG AG. He also served on the board at Burger King Holdings, Inc., Brunswick Corp., and Peet's Coffee & Tea, Inc.
He received his undergraduate degree from Universität zu Köln, an MBA from Harvard Business School, and a doctorate degree from Universität zu Köln.



